# Commit Messages

Use Conventional Commits. Keep the subject **under 72 chars**, **imperative mood**, **lowercase scope**.

## Allowed types

`feat` · `fix` · `refactor` · `perf` · `docs` · `test` · `chore` · `build` · `ci` · `style`

## Examples

- `feat(transakcije): add transaction split functionality`
- `fix(import): handle Raiffeisen decimal separator`
- `refactor(db): extract category queries into lib`
- `docs(arch): update multi-currency section`
- `test(actions): cover transfer detection`
- `chore(deps): bump supabase-js to 2.50`

## Guidelines

- One logical change per commit — don't mix unrelated work.
- Scope is the affected area (`import`, `transakcije`, `deps`, `cursor`, ...).
- Body is optional; use it to explain **why**, not what.
